4. Formal Mathematical Specification
4.1 Temporal State Vector
S(t)=\{ A(t),B(t),C(t)\} 
4.2 CTC Temporal Operator
T:S(t)\rightarrow S(t+1)

4.3 Retroactive Reinterpretation
R:S(t+1)\rightarrow S(t)
R(S(t+1))\neq S(t)
4.4 Temporal Drift
C'(t)=C(t)+\delta (t)
4.5 3AC Compatibility
T(3AC(S))\mathrm{\  remains\  stable\  under\  recursion}

5. Boundary Clauses
Clause 1: Temporal Primacy
All symbolic and interpretive operations must respect CTC’s temporal primitives.
Clause 2: Non‑Reversibility
Retroactive reinterpretation modifies interpretations, not historical states.
Clause 3: Drift Containment
||\delta (t)||<\epsilon 
Clause 4: Symbolic Compliance
B‑Layer operators cannot generate temporal structures not permitted by CTC.
Clause 5: Interpretive Coherence
A‑Layer constructs must remain coherent under recursive temporal updates.


